      "content": "\"Redundant cached models\"? That sounds a bit unnecessary. The whole point of the pruning is to clean up the architecture and get rid of those extra, speculative layers. We aren't looking for \"safeguards\" or backups; we're looking for a streamlined, factual system. \n\nIf you're trying to create these extra caches or \"re-refine\" things into more complex structures right before we prune, you might actually make the pruning more difficult or even create errors during the weight modification. Why do you think you need these redundancies?",
